Interface ShippingMethodByIdFetch

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Fetch<ShippingMethod>, FetchDsl<ShippingMethod,ShippingMethodByIdFetch>, MetaModelExpansionDsl<ShippingMethod,ShippingMethodByIdFetch,ShippingMethodExpansionModel<ShippingMethod>>, MetaModelFetchDsl<ShippingMethod,ShippingMethodByIdFetch,ShippingMethodExpansionModel<ShippingMethod>>, ReferenceExpandeable<ShippingMethod>, ReferenceExpandeableDsl<ShippingMethod,ShippingMethodByIdFetch>, SphereRequest<java.util.Optional<ShippingMethod>>

    public interface ShippingMethodByIdFetch
extends MetaModelFetchDsl<ShippingMethod,ShippingMethodByIdFetch,ShippingMethodExpansionModel<ShippingMethod>>
    Fetches a shipping method by ID. 
    withShippingMethod(client(), shippingMethod -> {
    final ShippingMethodByIdFetch fetch = ShippingMethodByIdFetch.of(shippingMethod.getId());
    final String actualFetchedId = execute(fetch).get().getId();
    assertThat(actualFetchedId).isEqualTo(shippingMethod.getId());
});

      • plusExpansionPaths

        ShippingMethodByIdFetch plusExpansionPaths(java.util.function.Function<ShippingMethodExpansionModel<ShippingMethod>,ExpansionPath<ShippingMethod>> m)
        Description copied from interface: MetaModelExpansionDsl
        Creates a new object with the properties of the old object but adds a new expansion path to it by using meta models.

        An example in the product projection context:

        final ProductProjectionByIdFetch fetch1 = ProductProjectionByIdFetch.of("id", ProductProjectionType.CURRENT)
        .plusExpansionPaths(m -> m.categories());
assertThat(fetch1.expansionPaths())
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]")));

final ProductProjectionByIdFetch fetch2 = fetch1.plusExpansionPaths(m -> m.productType());
assertThat(fetch2.expansionPaths())
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]"), ExpansionPath.of("productType")))
        .isEqualTo(listOf(fetch1.expansionPaths(), ExpansionPath.of("productType")));

//this is equivalent to

final ExpansionPath<ProductProjection> categoryExpand = ProductProjectionExpansionModel.of().categories();
final ExpansionPath<ProductProjection> productTypeExpand = ProductProjectionExpansionModel.of().productType();
final ProductProjectionByIdFetch fetchB = ProductProjectionByIdFetch.of("id", ProductProjectionType.CURRENT)
                .withExpansionPaths(asList(categoryExpand, productTypeExpand));
assertThat(fetchB.expansionPaths())
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]"), ExpansionPath.of("productType")));

      • withExpansionPaths

        ShippingMethodByIdFetch withExpansionPaths(java.util.function.Function<ShippingMethodExpansionModel<ShippingMethod>,ExpansionPath<ShippingMethod>> m)
        Description copied from interface: MetaModelExpansionDsl
        Creates a new object with the properties of the old object but replaces all expansion paths with a single expansionPath by using meta models.

        An example in the product projection context:

        final ProductProjectionByIdFetch fetch = ProductProjectionByIdFetch.of("id", ProductProjectionType.CURRENT)
                .plusExpansionPaths(ProductProjectionExpansionModel.of().categories());

assertThat(fetch.expansionPaths())
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]")));

final ProductProjectionByIdFetch fetch2 =
        fetch.withExpansionPaths(m -> m.productType());

assertThat(fetch.expansionPaths()).overridingErrorMessage("old object is unchanged")
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]")));
assertThat(fetch2.expansionPaths()).isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("productType")));
assertThat(fetch2).isNotSameAs(fetch);

        See the test code.

        ShippingMethodByIdFetch plusExpansionPaths(ExpansionPath<ShippingMethod> expansionPath)
        Description copied from interface: ReferenceExpandeableDsl
        Creates a new object with the properties of the old object but adds expansionPath to the expansion paths.

        An example in the product projection context:

        final ProductProjectionByIdFetch fetch = ProductProjectionByIdFetch.of("id", ProductProjectionType.CURRENT);

assertThat(fetch.expansionPaths()).isEmpty();

        fetch.plusExpansionPaths(ProductProjectionExpansionModel.of().categories());

assertThat(fetch.expansionPaths()).overridingErrorMessage("old object is unchanged").isEmpty();
assertThat(fetch2.expansionPaths()).isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]")));
assertThat(fetch2).isNotSameAs(fetch);
